methods.name: a
javadoc: Returns a double[3] array with movement offsets, used to calculate trailing tail/neck positions. [0] = yaw offset, [1] = y offset, [2] = unused, always 0. Parameters: buffer index offset, partial ticks.

methods.name: a
javadoc: Find and return a path among the circles described by pathPoints, or null if the shortest path would just be directly between the start and finish with no intermediate points.

Starting with pathPoint[startIdx], it searches the neighboring points (and their neighboring points, and so on) until it reaches pathPoint[finishIdx], at which point it calls makePath to seal the deal.
